1
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:14,082
(crowd talking)

2
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:21,441
(murmuring)

3
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:25,322
(hit)

4
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:30,851
Narrator: This was the Open
when everything seemed to happen.

5
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,082
(upbeat music)

6
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:37,930
(fire crackling)

7
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:50,484
On the second day,
the boy Ballesteros was now six under par.

8
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:53,007
And led outright by two strokes.

9
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:56,642
(crowd applauding)

10
00:00:58,640 --> 00:01:03,521
But, inevitably, the power of world golf
had begun to close in.

11
00:01:03,680 --> 00:01:05,330
Gary Player.

12
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:07,084
Johnny Miller.

13
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:08,765
Jack Nicklaus.

14
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:14,811
Severiano Ballesteros, only nineteen.

15
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,970
(crowd applauding)

16
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:19,531
Everyone enjoying him

17
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:23,122
and waiting for him to vanish from the leaderboard.

18
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:27,009
I remember watching this "boy".

19
00:01:27,160 --> 00:01:32,200
I watched the way that he did things
and it was a little bit unique.

20
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:34,370
(crowd applauding)

21
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:37,285
Here was this young guy ﬂashing a ball,

22
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:40,205
playing great recoveries and holing the putts

23
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:44,524
<i>and a great smile and I said:
"This is a very special young man."</i>

24
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:50,680
We all thought, who the devil
is this young matador of the links?

25
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:52,882
Broadcaster: Straight in the middle.

26
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:56,886
Peter Allies: And of course his story was
quite extraordinary.

27
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:59,122
(crowd applauding)

28
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:01,362
(soothing piano music)

29
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:12,242
(rhythmic guitar joins in)

30
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,371
Seve: My love was always playing golf.

31
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,531
Apart from golf, nothing existed for me.

32
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:27,845
Nothing.

33
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:41,610
(ﬂute joins in) (men shouting in Spanish)

34
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:05,722
(men shout louder)

35
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,682
(cheering)

36
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:21,049
Father:

37
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:54,722
(music fades out)

38
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:40,002
Brother:

39
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:06,722
(man singing a capella)

40
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:29,808
There's the church, right here.

41
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,770
It's pretty old.

42
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:36,249
And the school is on the right.

43
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,970
Right here.

44
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,690
There's my school.

45
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:47,006
The golf course is right here.
Here is the sixth hole, down there.

46
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,083
There's bad roads here, eh.

47
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:57,402
(soft acoustic guitar music)

48
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:07,488
That's where I lived.

49
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:12,726
Seve: The house is about 100 years old
and it was a quite solid house I think.

50
00:06:12,880 --> 00:06:16,123
My father, he was a farmer.

51
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:23,771
My father really worked very hard
but my mother worked even harder.

52
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:27,845
She spent all her life for the family.

53
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:35,165
Seve:

54
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:39,291
Brother:

55
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:46,243
Brother:

56
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,642
(cows mooing)

57
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,962
(chicken cackles)

58
00:07:11,960 --> 00:07:14,042
(clanging)

59
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:51,291
Mother:

60
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,082
(acoustic guitar music)

61
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:39,922
(waves crashing)

62
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:45,246
Seve: There's many ways to play golf.

63
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:48,520
You can build your own golf course

64
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:51,729
by using your imagination-- wife all.

65
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:17,043
Seve: Well, because I was not allowed
to play or practice on the golf course,

66
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,810
I used to play on the beach.

67
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:41,129
I used to practice seven, eight hours per day.

68
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:52,003
No!

69
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:53,969
(Splashes)

70
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:10,322
(sewing machine rattles)

71
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,210
Mother:

72
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:54,888
(fade in; applause)

73
00:10:56,000 --> 00:11:00,847
Broadcaster: Severiano Ballesteros,
only nineteen coming here this morning,

74
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,446
leading a field of world-class golfers.

75
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:08,246
<i>Never before, in the history of this great championship,</i>

76
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:11,324
had a Spaniard been leading the whole field.

77
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:15,491
Yes! It's right in the middle of the hole.

78
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:20,968
<i>He's realty tweaking their noses.
What great stuff from this youngster.</i>

79
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:26,210
Can Ballesteros possibly make it?

80
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,488
He's newborn into world-class golf

81
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:32,611
and some say this very innocence
makes him oblivious to pressure.

82
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:34,765
(hit)

83
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:42,323
Seve: <i>First, a' was hitting the bah'
ah' over the place</i>

84
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:45,563
<i>and started making double bogies and triple bogies</i>

85
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:47,046
Broadcaster: Oh, oh, oh.

86
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:53,487
Wife. That's in trouble.

87
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:05,088
Ballesteros battling to get back into second place

88
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:08,762
but he's got a long, long putt here for an Eagle three.

89
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,924
Right in for an Eagle.

90
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:19,243
Quite astonishing, this young Spanish player.

91
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:24,046
Miller actually congratulates him on that monster putt.

92
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:32,600
No, he wants to get it in two more from here

93
00:12:32,760 --> 00:12:35,286
to tie with Nicklaus for second place.

94
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:44,401
I said he was about the only one that I
saw coming along that really impressed me.

95
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:49,361
He was tremendous around the green.
He had a lot of imagination.

96
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:52,450
Broadcaster: Yes!

97
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,170
(applause)

98
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:56,846
Broadcaster: Absolutely marvellous!

99
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,770
Straight in the middle!

100
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:09,767
What a prospect for the future and what
an exciting end to this championship.

101
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:15,001
That great chip-and-run
between the bunkers on eighteen,

102
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:18,926
man, that's a great shot.
I was very impressed with that.

103
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,328
(applause)

104
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:40,371
Señoras y señores, muchas gracias...

105
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:42,602
(crowd laughs and applauds)

106
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:51,280
Broadcaster: He may have made a heart
throb among the girls of Southport...

107
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:11,882
(acoustic guitar music)

108
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:50,362
(bell rings)

109
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,928
(voice fades out)

110
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,605
Seve: In my mind,

111
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:10,563
I always dreamed and I always visualized
myself as becoming a champion.

112
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:18,169
Broadcaster: Ballesteros is just about
to enter Leven's tigerish finish.

113
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,641
It's good. It's got the tail wind.

114
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:29,325
Oh yes! And the young matador
ls absolutely delighted!

115
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:32,848
Against all the odds he takes the outright lead yer again

116
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,571
and can't wait to get to the next hole.

117
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:39,767
Strong breeze, so it's rather bold...

118
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:41,490
(applause)

119
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,688
Broadcaster: He ﬂipped that one up.

120
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:47,563
He's running, he's jumping, he's hurling.

121
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:53,409
He really is charged up. This is what it
means by having your adrenaline ﬂowing.

122
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:56,131
He had a great walk about him. His gait.

123
00:15:57,400 --> 00:16:00,290
He just strolled like a champion.

124
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:03,209
(hit)

125
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:07,081
Broadcaster: Well he's over on the
right-hand side somewhere.

126
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:09,368
Looks like he's in the parking lot.

127
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:15,401
Yes, he's certainly in the car park.
He's right up against the cars here.

128
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:18,090
So where must I drop?

129
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:24,202
You take the nearest point giving you
complete relief, no nearer the hole.

130
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:27,887
- Well it must be over there, right?
- Wife correct.

131
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:33,285
Seve: Over the years I've been called
the car park champion.

132
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:35,010
(hit)

133
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:38,209
Interviewer: Do you resent that?
Do you mind that?

134
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:40,601
Seve: Golf is not how, it's how many.

135
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:51,921
Broadcaster: Two putts from here
to remain two ahead.

136
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:55,408
Crowd: Oh! Whoa! Yeah!
(applause)

137
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:57,927
Broadcaster: And he only needs one!

138
00:16:59,240 --> 00:17:04,201
Well, the golfing gods really are
with the smiling Spaniard today.

139
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:10,726
Hale Irwin, who was two shots ahead, out of it now.

140
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:15,050
But perhaps we are just moments away
from Severiano Ballesteros

141
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:18,841
becoming the youngest Open champion of this century.

142
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,485
(hit)

143
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:26,803
Broadcaster: He's played it out safely for
the front of the green.

144
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,810
(crowd cheering)

145
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:38,566
Broadcaster: Irwin going through the crowd
and surrendering.

146
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:43,601
Somewhere back in the mass, Ballesteros
still battling his way through.

147
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:57,522
(mild applause)

148
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:03,643
<i>Broadcaster: And what a finish!
What a grandstand finish yet again</i>

149
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:05,689
from the young Spanish wizard.

150
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:09,730
(applause)

151
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:13,327
Broadcaster: Ballesteros is the champion!

152
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:17,724
Interviewer: Who were the two men who
came up and threw their arms around you?

153
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:21,123
Seve: My brothers.
We are all the brothers here.

154
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:29,162
Please, he hasn't yet recorded.
He hasn't yet recorded.

155
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:33,450
Seve: Having all three of my brothers
there with me and supporting me

156
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:36,809
and seeing all of them just running through the green

157
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:40,282
and giving me a big hug-
and I saw my brother crying.

158
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:46,441
They realized that I did something very important.

159
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:49,405
Broadcaster: Severiano Ballesteros...

160
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:52,171
(applause)

161
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:24,802
(crowd cheering)

162
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:40,123
Seve: It never crossed my mind
to finish second.

163
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:42,527
Second... no one would remember.

164
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:45,890
I have to be the champion.

165
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,969
Mother:

166
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:12,524
Seve, Seve, Seve...

167
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:17,247
Seve: I missed school many, many days.

168
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:20,882
My father and my mother think I go to school,

169
00:22:21,040 --> 00:22:24,044
but most of the days I didn't go.

170
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:26,441
I'd make a little turn to the left.

171
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:29,202
(acoustic guitar music)

172
00:22:34,480 --> 00:22:38,371
Seve: Playing golf with only one club,
you see, a three iron,

173
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:42,889
that really helped me a lot because, you know,

174
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:45,884
I have to hit all kinds of shots with only one club.

175
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:49,123
I have to putt, I have to drive with the three iron.

176
00:22:49,280 --> 00:22:53,001
That is why I have a very good ability, you know.

177
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:59,127
If you play with only one club, it makes you think...

178
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:20,611
(piano jazz music)
Broadcaster: April.

179
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:28,886
Georgia. USA.
It's Masters time again.

180
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:32,083
(hit)

181
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:36,766
Paired with Gary Player in this final round

182
00:23:36,920 --> 00:23:41,687
is 21 years old today Spanish star Severiano Ballesteros.

183
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:45,561
Winner of twenty professional tournaments around the globe

184
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:47,927
before he even got the key to the door.

185
00:23:48,080 --> 00:23:52,369
Seve: Gary Player was always my hero.

186
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:55,524
And I wished already that we were friends.

187
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:57,842
He is like my father.

188
00:23:59,120 --> 00:24:03,170
He was pulling so hard for me to win
and that's a nice feeling.

189
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:08,451
When I holed that putt he walked across
the green with a million people watching

190
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:14,289
<i>and he put his arm around me and he said:
"Got it. You reached me to win Masters."</i>

191
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:19,691
Broadcaster: And here's the pride of
Europe, Severiano Ballesteros.

192
00:24:19,840 --> 00:24:22,810
Number seventeen, from about fifteen feet.

193
00:24:25,040 --> 00:24:26,610
(applause)

194
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:30,162
Broadcaster:
Olé, and all is well with the world!

195
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:35,048
This for a sixty-eight
and a seven stroke lead once again.

196
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:38,682
And there it is, one more time!

197
00:24:38,840 --> 00:24:41,810
The magic touch of a man, who not many years ago,

198
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:44,367
owned little more than an old three iron

199
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:48,525
and the certainty that some day,
he'd become a champion at this game.

200
00:24:49,480 --> 00:24:53,929
And there it is.
Comfortably parring number 16 and 17.

201
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:56,651
And here, triumphantly, number 18,

202
00:24:56,800 --> 00:25:01,840
Seve Ballesteros, 23 years and four days
old, of Santander, Spain,

203
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:05,482
played one third of the 72 holes under par.

204
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:09,565
A record, to become both
the youngest winner of the Masters

205
00:25:09,720 --> 00:25:12,041
and the first from Europe.

206
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:15,010
Son of a farmer, youngest of four brothers

207
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:18,329
and still living in the house where he was born.

208
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:20,770
Severiano Ballesteros!

209
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:22,888
(applause)

210
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:25,651
Broadcaster: The 1980 Masters champion!

211
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:29,607
Olé indeed.

212
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:35,122
His agent, Ed Barnard told us
that he had been at a luncheon

213
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:39,683
and he, the agent,
was introduced by the toast-master

214
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:45,404
as the manager of professional golfer
Ballerina Sevasteros.

215
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:49,566
<i>Announcer:
The</i> winner <i>of the forty-fourth Masters...</i>

216
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:53,566
Broadcaster: They butchered his name
a week ago, but no longer.

217
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:57,122
When you win the Masters, they get your name fight.

218
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,891
Father:

219
00:26:06,760 --> 00:26:08,091
Mother:

220
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:10,044
- Hola, mama'.
- Hola, hijo.

221
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:11,725
Hula, papa'.

222
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:53,322
(scrubbing)

223
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:48,131
<i>Seve: Because I was the smallest, I used
to do ab' the dirty work for everybody.</i>

224
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:54,208
I remember I used to clean up the shoes on Sunday morning

225
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:57,927
and they used to give me five pesetas.

226
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:03,882
(piano and string music)

227
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:14,686
Brother:

228
00:28:29,400 --> 00:28:30,526
Seve:

229
00:28:34,560 --> 00:28:37,040
Brother:

230
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:22,201
Seve: I started to caddy when I was nine.
At the beginning it was very good.

231
00:29:35,080 --> 00:29:40,405
Seve: But I think it's a little boring
to carry a golf bag to a very bad golfer.

232
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:46,124
Because they go left, right, you have to
try and find the ball. It's very boring.

233
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:52,286
But as soon as I started practicing I enjoyed it very much

234
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:58,049
and every time the members didn't see me,
I'd hit the ball or make a few swings.

235
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:33,608
(chuckles)

236
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:47,721
(hit)

237
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:04,969
Seve: I played at night when it was dark.
Nobody saw me. On the beach.

238
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:13,526
Maybe the strict rules helped me because
I was more anxious and hungry to practice.

239
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:17,922
And the more difficult the thing, the more you try.

240
00:31:20,560 --> 00:31:23,006
(hit)

241
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:25,482
(applause fades in)

242
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:30,168
Broadcaster: And what a finish!
What a grandstand finish yet again!

243
00:31:30,360 --> 00:31:32,727
Are you aware of the noise of the crowd

244
00:31:32,880 --> 00:31:36,521
when you concentrate on
the last hole of such a tournament?

245
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:40,765
Seve: No. If your concentration is good,
you don't hear anything.

246
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:42,485
Nothing worries you.

247
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:47,328
But ff your concentration is not good,
even the ﬂies can bother you.

248
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:08,642
Seve: Golf has always been fun.

249
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:13,969
The good thing about golf is that when you play golf

250
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:18,370
you always produce one or two shots

251
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:21,364
that really make you feel good

252
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:28,050
and makes you think
"Oh, I think I'll come back tomorrow."

253
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:29,850
(applause)

254
00:32:33,440 --> 00:32:35,010
(Splash)

255
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:45,247
(acoustic guitar music reprises)

256
00:32:52,560 --> 00:32:55,530
Interviewer:
Were you a well-behaved kid, Seve?

257
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:58,047
Wife, I'd never get in any trouble. wife.

258
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:02,243
Well yes... one time I...

259
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,645
(laughs)

260
00:33:04,800 --> 00:33:05,847
Teacher

261
00:33:42,600 --> 00:33:44,170
(slaps)

262
00:33:52,440 --> 00:33:54,010
(slams door)

263
00:33:56,520 --> 00:33:58,090
(slow string music)

264
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:27,010
Mama'?

265
