00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:58,410
Seve: This is the place in my house
where I used to practice when I was young.

275
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:01,609
Because sometimes there's bad weather here.

276
00:37:04,040 --> 00:37:07,487
And I didn't have any other place to practice.

277
00:37:07,640 --> 00:37:10,211
Interviewer: You used to have a net there?

278
00:37:10,360 --> 00:37:14,649
Yes. Now I don't know where it is,
but I used to put it up here.

279
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:18,207
(acoustic guitar music reprises)

280
00:37:54,240 --> 00:37:56,242
Mother:

281
00:37:56,400 --> 00:38:00,166
Seve: I used to practice at twelve,
one o'clock at night.

282
00:38:01,040 --> 00:38:05,284
My mother used to come down many times
and say: "Come up and go to sleep.

283
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:07,681
What are you doing here?
You're crazy!"

284
00:38:08,600 --> 00:38:10,170
(sighs)

285
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:12,971
It was good... a good place to practice.

286
00:38:18,040 --> 00:38:20,646
(people talking)

287
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:55,282
Seve: I used to wait for the guard
and the caddy masters

288
00:38:55,880 --> 00:39:01,171
and the guy from the locker room to go by
to make sure that everything was clear.

289
00:39:02,720 --> 00:39:06,042
Once they went through...
I jumped.

290
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:16,602
(grunts) (laughs)

291
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:20,482
(upbeat music reprises)

292
00:39:28,360 --> 00:39:29,930
(applause fades in)

293
00:39:30,080 --> 00:39:35,041
Broadcaster: When you've got it--
you've got it! What a magnificent touch.

294
00:39:48,880 --> 00:39:50,769
(crowd cheers)

295
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:05,001
(crowd cheers)

296
00:40:09,520 --> 00:40:11,602
(inaudible cheers)

297
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:16,282
(applause)

298
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:23,882
Broadcaster: Ladies and gentlemen, the
greatest golfer in the world!

299
00:40:24,040 --> 00:40:25,610
Severiano Ballesteros!

300
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:27,683
(music fades out)

301
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:45,682
(moving)

302
00:41:51,080 --> 00:41:53,560
Father: Vamos a casa, chicas, vamos.

303
00:41:54,800 --> 00:41:56,882
(moving)

304
00:42:47,040 --> 00:42:49,008
(acoustic guitar music)

305
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:50,207
Doctor:

306
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:15,124
When he stepped up to the ball, we knew
something exciting was going to happen.

307
00:43:15,840 --> 00:43:17,410
(hit)

308
00:43:18,320 --> 00:43:20,322
He was so aggressive in his drive.

309
00:43:20,480 --> 00:43:22,767
If there was a green over there at 3-20,

310
00:43:22,920 --> 00:43:28,131
he'd hit it 300 yards through the air
which was pretty impressive in that era.

311
00:43:36,200 --> 00:43:40,808
Seve: I took more risks than most people,
but that is my way.

312
00:43:45,200 --> 00:43:47,601
Nick Faldo: The way he played shots,

313
00:43:47,760 --> 00:43:50,240
and the way he swung the club,

314
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:52,482
was beautiful.

315
00:43:52,640 --> 00:43:57,362
Ben Crenshaw: He had one of the most
beautiful set-ups I have ever seen.

316
00:43:58,760 --> 00:44:01,366
He had a style all of his own.

317
00:44:04,680 --> 00:44:07,365
He could get it up and down from the trashcan.

318
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:11,605
From the garage. From the car park.
You name it, he can do it.

319
00:44:13,720 --> 00:44:18,282
Ben Crenshaw: But his shod shots were
just something to behold.

320
00:44:18,440 --> 00:44:22,490
What a wonderful touch he had with
his hands and how creative he was.

321
00:44:22,680 --> 00:44:27,686
He was more like an artist painting
on a beautiful canvas around the green.

322
00:44:27,840 --> 00:44:30,969
Seve: It's something
that is very hard to describe.

323
00:44:31,120 --> 00:44:34,522
This feeling I have.
You feel it and you think about that.

324
00:44:34,680 --> 00:44:37,445
You visualize that and you feel it inside.

325
00:44:37,600 --> 00:44:39,125
And then you do it”.

326
00:44:40,160 --> 00:44:42,811
There's no secret. This is the way it is.

327
00:44:47,800 --> 00:44:49,370
Man: Muy bien.

328
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:52,242
Seve:

329
00:45:05,880 --> 00:45:07,962
(cheering fades in)

330
00:45:08,120 --> 00:45:11,841
Certain people in life have this little aura around them.

331
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:14,731
Sinatra had it.
Elvis Presley had it.

332
00:45:14,880 --> 00:45:18,248
Geordie Best had it.
And he had it. It just oozed from him.

333
00:45:19,840 --> 00:45:23,242
Everywhere he went, there was just this trail of people.

334
00:45:23,400 --> 00:45:24,925
"Have you seen Seve?"

335
00:45:25,080 --> 00:45:29,881
He was like a film star--
"Have you seen the latest Clint Eastwood movie?"

336
00:45:30,080 --> 00:45:32,208
He had that something about him.

337
00:45:33,880 --> 00:45:38,442
Seve: The only thing that at first
made me a bit worried is the attention

338
00:45:38,600 --> 00:45:42,207
that was created very quickly from the media

339
00:45:42,360 --> 00:45:48,163
and from being a nobody to becoming
a superstar in just a few days, you know.

340
00:45:49,240 --> 00:45:51,891
My freedom disappeared.

341
00:45:54,240 --> 00:45:55,810
Especially in the UK.

342
00:45:58,520 --> 00:46:00,648
I was so popular.

343
00:46:00,800 --> 00:46:06,091
Broadcaster: This young Ballesteros
has suddenly become the crowd's hero.

344
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:10,251
Peter Allies: The British public
absolutely loved him,

345
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:14,166
his style, his charisma, his looks and everything.

346
00:46:14,320 --> 00:46:15,845
And he loved them.

347
00:46:16,560 --> 00:46:21,282
Guys, if you don't mind please.
I know you're nervous but I am too, okay.

348
00:46:21,440 --> 00:46:23,010
(they laugh)

349
00:46:23,160 --> 00:46:25,891
Broadcaster:
A little movement in the crowd.

350
00:46:29,480 --> 00:46:31,608
(crowd laughs and claps)

351
00:46:32,520 --> 00:46:36,730
Broadcaster: I think he saw that guy
as he popped it back inside there.

352
00:46:36,880 --> 00:46:40,043
When Seve turned around and:
"Nope. Not me. No."

353
00:46:40,920 --> 00:46:42,490
Lovely.

354
00:46:43,360 --> 00:46:47,285
Seve: I have to do nearly everything
in my room in the hotel.

355
00:46:47,440 --> 00:46:51,604
And that was tough for a young man
like me, you know. Very tough.

356
00:46:53,280 --> 00:46:57,365
But that was the price of the success.

357
00:47:01,560 --> 00:47:03,767
(hit)

358
00:47:04,520 --> 00:47:06,648
(cows moo)

359
00:47:45,240 --> 00:47:46,890
(cow moos)

360
00:47:47,960 --> 00:47:49,769
(hit)

361
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:54,164
(cow moos)

362
00:48:04,840 --> 00:48:07,571
(acoustic guitar music reprises)

363
00:48:07,720 --> 00:48:12,408
Broadcaster: There's certainly no
holding back over these finishing holes.

364
00:48:12,560 --> 00:48:17,805
He's just lashing at the bail with every
ounce of power in his substantial body.

365
00:48:19,560 --> 00:48:21,130
Number two. Par five.

366
00:48:24,200 --> 00:48:26,282
(applause)

367
00:48:36,000 --> 00:48:37,525
(crowd cheering)

368
00:48:37,720 --> 00:48:40,929
Broadcaster: Well done.
Slam bam! Birdie. Eagle.

369
00:48:41,080 --> 00:48:43,560
And suddenly, after being a shot astray,

370
00:48:43,720 --> 00:48:47,486
Seve Ballesteros is leading the Masters by two strokes.

371
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:51,845
(hit)

372
00:48:54,440 --> 00:48:58,365
Broadcaster: And isn't this just
the most unbelievable golf?

373
00:49:02,600 --> 00:49:05,251
And it looks absolutely dead on the pin.

374
00:49:07,880 --> 00:49:10,247
Oh my goodness gracious!

375
00:49:10,400 --> 00:49:15,167
Where does a man get the moxy to hit
a shot like that at a moment like this?

376
00:49:15,320 --> 00:49:17,402
(applause)

377
00:49:21,560 --> 00:49:25,565
Seve: Because the Americans
always believed until later on

378
00:49:25,720 --> 00:49:29,725
that it was not possible
for any European to win the Masters,

379
00:49:29,880 --> 00:49:33,441
it makes me feel very happy and very proud.

380
00:49:33,600 --> 00:49:36,490
(crowd cheering)

381
00:49:37,600 --> 00:49:41,810
Broadcaster: I guess it was meant for him
to be the champion.

382
00:49:43,360 --> 00:49:48,002
When he went to Augusta,
he broke some barriers for us, certainly.

383
00:49:48,160 --> 00:49:52,245
After him winning, it spurred on an
incredible European run.

384
00:49:53,400 --> 00:49:58,201
Seve: You're supposed to wear
the green jacket only during the Masters.

385
00:49:59,240 --> 00:50:00,810
(applause)

386
00:50:00,960 --> 00:50:05,761
Broadcaster: Severiano Ballesteros,
the 1983 Masters Champion.

387
00:50:08,120 --> 00:50:11,966
I took it home and... don't tell anybody,
ifs in my house.

388
00:50:12,120 --> 00:50:15,488
This is a replica, okay?
You understand?

