00:51:48,040 --> 00:51:51,761
Seve: You can really know
which way the ball goes.

401
00:51:51,960 --> 00:51:55,567
Not only by sound, but also by feel.

402
00:51:55,720 --> 00:51:57,290
(hit)

403
00:51:57,440 --> 00:51:59,124
Seve: That helps.

404
00:52:18,840 --> 00:52:19,887
Rafa:

405
00:52:22,480 --> 00:52:23,891
Seve:

406
00:52:28,520 --> 00:52:30,602
Seve: First, you need the ability.

407
00:52:30,760 --> 00:52:34,048
But I think the mental side is very important, too.

408
00:52:35,800 --> 00:52:39,566
You have to be cool.
You have to be very powerful.

409
00:52:40,800 --> 00:52:45,806
You have to be convinced
that you have a great chance to win.

410
00:52:51,520 --> 00:52:56,686
Seve: You can lose, but it must never
cross your mind. Always winning.

411
00:52:56,840 --> 00:53:00,890
<i>It's very important to keep
your face down. Don't took around.</i>

412
00:53:01,040 --> 00:53:04,931
Don't ever put your face up.
Talk as little as you can.

413
00:53:05,960 --> 00:53:09,407
And just put your eyes with your ball and the hole.

414
00:53:12,320 --> 00:53:16,962
Man: He wouldn't exchange too many
pleasantries when he was playing.

415
00:53:17,120 --> 00:53:18,770
Obviously he was out to win.

416
00:53:18,960 --> 00:53:22,567
A great champ is not concerned with anyone else.

417
00:53:22,760 --> 00:53:28,324
Broadcaster: Now Ballesteros--
I'm sure we're going to see a savage smash.

418
00:53:28,480 --> 00:53:32,565
Just look out, ball.
You don't know what you're in for...

419
00:53:32,720 --> 00:53:35,326
(hits)

420
00:53:35,520 --> 00:53:37,602
Broadcaster: I say' "Take that!"

421
00:53:42,080 --> 00:53:43,650
Seve: Mierda!

422
00:53:44,400 --> 00:53:46,926
Broadcaster:
He may be slightly cross...

423
00:53:47,080 --> 00:53:49,481
Those cold, black eyes are burning.

424
00:53:50,000 --> 00:53:52,128
(swears in Spanish)

425
00:53:55,560 --> 00:54:00,521
Seve: You never know what is going to
happen with me on each hole.

426
00:54:01,480 --> 00:54:03,767
Rafa:

427
00:54:05,840 --> 00:54:08,889
(rhythmic acoustic guitar music)

428
00:54:09,040 --> 00:54:13,011
Broadcaster: We have found Seve's ball,
but he really is in a dreadful position.

429
00:54:13,160 --> 00:54:15,686
He's right in the middle of that willow scrub.

430
00:54:15,840 --> 00:54:17,365
Move back, please.

431
00:54:19,240 --> 00:54:21,811
Seve: No, I'm not a very steady player.

432
00:54:25,280 --> 00:54:26,805
Move back, please.

433
00:54:27,680 --> 00:54:32,481
Seve: The people like to see troubled
shots in the trees and the bunkers,

434
00:54:32,640 --> 00:54:36,281
and see me make bogies,
double-bogies, you know.

435
00:54:36,440 --> 00:54:41,401
<i>But I think one day I hit all my drives
straight to the fairway</i>

436
00:54:41,560 --> 00:54:44,723
The people will have lost a lot of golf probably.

437
00:54:47,760 --> 00:54:52,129
<i>I always say that every time that I go to the rough,</i>

438
00:54:52,280 --> 00:54:54,601
many times I can swing the club.

439
00:54:55,680 --> 00:54:59,162
I always believe that there is always a shot somewhere.

440
00:54:59,320 --> 00:55:01,448
(hit) (applause)

441
00:55:17,280 --> 00:55:20,045
Seve: I've always been
very hard on myself,

442
00:55:20,200 --> 00:55:23,204
even when I fumed professional in my early days.

443
00:55:25,080 --> 00:55:28,721
Seve: When I was having a bad day,
I would say to myself:

444
00:55:28,880 --> 00:55:32,327
<i>"Today you didn't do a good job, you didn't play well,</i>

445
00:55:32,480 --> 00:55:37,168
so you don't deserve to have dinner."
So I went to bed without having dinner.

446
00:55:38,560 --> 00:55:41,166
That's one way to be hard on yourself...

447
00:55:41,320 --> 00:55:43,448
(hit) (Sighs)

448
00:55:43,600 --> 00:55:48,322
Broadcaster: When he was in the doldrums,
nobody could have looked sadder.

449
00:55:48,480 --> 00:55:52,849
You wanted to cuddle him and take him home
and let Mom make him tea.

450
00:55:53,000 --> 00:55:57,210
Seve: When I play bad,
I feel bad not only for myself

451
00:55:57,360 --> 00:56:00,682
I feel very bad for the people who've come to watch.

452
00:56:02,720 --> 00:56:06,202
When you start having some kind of failure,

453
00:56:06,360 --> 00:56:10,570
that's when you start getting tight and you get worried.

454
00:56:10,760 --> 00:56:16,324
And it's like "I don't want to miss the
putt", not "I want to make the putt".

455
00:56:16,480 --> 00:56:22,010
Broadcaster: That's on line--
has it got the legs? Oh no, caramba.

456
00:56:22,160 --> 00:56:24,845
Another Spanish cries.

457
00:56:26,160 --> 00:56:28,242
Sever It's all in the mind.

