01:01:49,120 --> 01:01:50,963
Father:

487
01:01:58,520 --> 01:02:03,208
Seve: To have success wherever
you play golf or do any other thing,

488
01:02:03,400 --> 01:02:06,324
there are two things you need.

489
01:02:06,480 --> 01:02:10,246
<i>You have to work very hard--</i>
<i>that's number one.</i>

490
01:02:10,400 --> 01:02:14,405
And number two, you need a tremendous amount of discipline.

491
01:02:17,080 --> 01:02:20,721
Discipline is the key in life.
For many things.

492
01:02:21,400 --> 01:02:22,970
(hit)

493
01:02:24,360 --> 01:02:30,163
Seve: You have to take care of yourself.
You have to sleep eight hours every day.

494
01:02:30,320 --> 01:02:35,247
And practice-- I go to the driving range
many times when I don't feel like it.

495
01:02:36,880 --> 01:02:40,965
You know what will be the best thing
for me for how I feel at the moment?

496
01:02:41,120 --> 01:02:43,088
I'd like to go to the hotel.

497
01:02:43,240 --> 01:02:47,723
My boy is there and I would like to be
there and play with my boy.

498
01:02:47,880 --> 01:02:51,009
But do you know what?
Lam going to the driving range.

499
01:02:51,960 --> 01:02:56,090
Because I know that tomorrow is a big day
and I wan! to be ready.

500
01:02:57,440 --> 01:02:59,044
That's the profession.

501
01:03:01,640 --> 01:03:03,210
(hit)

502
01:03:06,920 --> 01:03:08,445
(hit)

503
01:03:09,200 --> 01:03:12,647
Broadcaster: Touch of class, baby.
Touch of class.

504
01:03:14,400 --> 01:03:16,528
(applause)

505
01:03:20,280 --> 01:03:23,045
<i>Seve: Winning the Open is very difficult.</i>

506
01:03:24,120 --> 01:03:28,409
Winning the Open at Si. Andrews
was something very, very special.

507
01:03:28,560 --> 01:03:32,087
<i>Because St. Andrews is the home of golf,
and St. Andrews is...</i>

508
01:03:32,280 --> 01:03:36,251
is a different type of golf course.
It's a piece of art.

509
01:03:36,400 --> 01:03:40,325
Broadcaster: What a situation; Watson with
a putt for a birdie at the 13th,

510
01:03:40,480 --> 01:03:43,768
Ballesteros with a putt for a birdie at the 14th.

511
01:03:43,960 --> 01:03:45,485
Watson first.

512
01:03:50,120 --> 01:03:52,202
(crowd cheering)

513
01:03:53,200 --> 01:03:56,727
Broadcaster:
This would put him in a tie for the lead.

514
01:03:58,440 --> 01:04:01,046
Oh touché! (crowd cheering)

515
01:04:01,200 --> 01:04:07,162
Would you credit it. Two putts.
Two birdies. Still tied at 11 under par.

516
01:04:08,760 --> 01:04:11,047
Ballesteros, second and seventeen.

517
01:04:11,240 --> 01:04:12,765
(hit)

518
01:04:17,960 --> 01:04:20,406
(crowd starting to cheer)

519
01:04:20,560 --> 01:04:24,724
Broadcaster: Whoa whoa whoa,
that's a marvellous shot.

520
01:04:24,920 --> 01:04:27,002
(applause)

521
01:04:27,840 --> 01:04:30,127
Broadcaster: Back on the 17th tee.

522
01:04:31,760 --> 01:04:32,807
(hit)

523
01:04:33,720 --> 01:04:37,930
Broadcaster: And he sent that off on the
perfect line.

524
01:04:41,520 --> 01:04:43,045
Very brave.

525
01:04:43,200 --> 01:04:44,770
(applause)

526
01:04:49,920 --> 01:04:52,924
Broadcaster: Seve for a three at 17.

527
01:04:55,280 --> 01:04:56,805
It's not tied yet.

528
01:04:58,120 --> 01:05:00,202
(applause)

529
01:05:04,840 --> 01:05:06,968
Broadcaster: That's the four.

530
01:05:09,600 --> 01:05:12,729
Watson in the ideal spot down the 17th.

531
01:05:12,880 --> 01:05:17,090
Seve's already played the hole, got a 4.
So much can happen on the 17th.

532
01:05:19,800 --> 01:05:21,325
Oh...

533
01:05:21,520 --> 01:05:23,045
(crowd groans)

534
01:05:24,560 --> 01:05:27,484
Broadcaster: Oh dear, oh dear, oh dear...

535
01:05:27,640 --> 01:05:30,211
Well, they did say it wasn't all over yet...

536
01:05:30,400 --> 01:05:33,449
That really was an extraordinary shot from Tom.

537
01:05:33,600 --> 01:05:36,809
Seve's second shot to the final hole.

538
01:05:38,640 --> 01:05:40,210
(hit)

539
01:05:40,360 --> 01:05:42,249
Broadcaster: The dust ﬂies.

540
01:05:43,800 --> 01:05:44,847
(crowd cheers)

541
01:05:45,040 --> 01:05:47,281
<i>Broadcaster: What a little sweetie!</i>

542
01:05:50,200 --> 01:05:53,921
Seve lining up a short-ish putt.

543
01:05:55,160 --> 01:05:56,730
This is for a 3.

544
01:05:57,800 --> 01:06:00,167
And he's just got his hole!

545
01:06:00,320 --> 01:06:02,163
(crowd is cheering loudly)

546
01:06:06,840 --> 01:06:09,810
Broadcaster:
You think he enjoyed that one?

547
01:06:11,840 --> 01:06:13,763
Go on, give him a kiss as well.

548
01:06:15,120 --> 01:06:16,804
That's fantastic stuff'.

549
01:06:23,400 --> 01:06:27,769
This is St. Andrews, '84.
The best moment of my career,

550
01:06:27,960 --> 01:06:31,851
so I thought that it was a good idea
to stamp that forever in my arm.

551
01:06:32,000 --> 01:06:35,368
Just there. Remember, Seve.
You're the best.

552
01:06:35,520 --> 01:06:37,602
(applause)

553
01:06:40,760 --> 01:06:42,888
(applause becomes louder)

554
01:06:48,880 --> 01:06:53,408
Seve: This is for my mother, who has come
to the Open for the first time.

555
01:06:53,560 --> 01:06:56,530
She is around here, I don't know...
somewhere.

556
01:06:58,000 --> 01:07:00,082
(upbeat mandolin music)

557
01:07:05,600 --> 01:07:07,682
(cries of seagulls)

558
01:07:29,040 --> 01:07:30,724
Brother:

559
01:07:52,120 --> 01:07:53,167
Seve:

560
01:08:11,160 --> 01:08:16,200
Interviewer: What are the ambitions you
have in life generally, away from golf?

561
01:08:16,400 --> 01:08:20,928
Seve: I don't know... I've been
only thinking about golf. That's it.

562
01:08:22,560 --> 01:08:25,211
Interviewer: Do you have a girlfriend?
- No.

563
01:08:25,960 --> 01:08:30,124
Many. I have many.
But no steady one.

564
01:08:31,080 --> 01:08:32,605
(hit)

565
01:08:32,760 --> 01:08:37,482
He's so golf-orientated that all he does
is just play golf, golf, golf...

566
01:08:37,640 --> 01:08:42,680
I think if I was Seve, I'd go out
to a few discotheques now and again

567
01:08:42,840 --> 01:08:45,286
and have a bit of fun, let yourself go.

568
01:08:48,240 --> 01:08:53,804
Interviewer: A lot of people would say,
I'd like to be married and have a family.

569
01:08:53,960 --> 01:08:57,203
Well probably, yeah. Good idea.

570
01:08:58,480 --> 01:09:04,522
He had those wonderful smouldering looks
that sent many pulses racing, I tell you.

571
01:09:04,680 --> 01:09:10,483
But he was a canny lad. And he married
his childhood sweetheart, Carmen.

572
01:09:10,640 --> 01:09:12,802
She was his golfing pupil.

573
01:09:13,000 --> 01:09:16,686
And they became man and wife
and had three children together.

574
01:09:45,480 --> 01:09:47,881
(soft guitar music)

575
01:11:26,400 --> 01:11:30,450
Brother:

576
01:11:30,600 --> 01:11:32,762
Seve:

577
01:11:32,920 --> 01:11:34,445
Brother:

578
01:11:34,640 --> 01:11:37,325
Brian Moore:
The story of Severiano Ballesteros

579
01:11:37,520 --> 01:11:40,444
is about a young Spaniard from a humble background

580
01:11:40,600 --> 01:11:43,809
who has become one of the most controversial golf players

581
01:11:43,960 --> 01:11:46,042
and an attraction for so many girls

582
01:11:46,200 --> 01:11:48,726
in golf galleries around the world.

583
01:11:48,880 --> 01:11:51,167
But he's most in the news these days

584
01:11:51,320 --> 01:11:54,688
through his demands for appearance money when he plays,

585
01:11:54,840 --> 01:11:59,562
at a time when golf organizers are seeking
to stop this son of payment.

586
01:12:00,320 --> 01:12:05,087
Seve: When you go to the golf course,
who are you going to watch?

587
01:12:06,040 --> 01:12:07,883
The best players, isn't it.

588
01:12:08,040 --> 01:12:09,565
(cheering)

589
01:12:09,760 --> 01:12:14,049
The best players bring the TV and
give the prestige to the tournament.

590
01:12:14,200 --> 01:12:17,329
And the best players bring the people to watch.

591
01:12:18,360 --> 01:12:24,003
If the sponsors want the best players,
they have to pay them. That's it.

592
01:12:24,160 --> 01:12:26,845
Interviewer:
But hasn't golf given you a lot else?

593
01:12:27,000 --> 01:12:29,207
Do you know how much I give to golf?

594
01:12:30,040 --> 01:12:34,250
I started when I was nine.
And since then...

595
01:12:34,400 --> 01:12:37,961
I live until right now, twenty-three.

596
01:12:39,200 --> 01:12:44,206
This way. All for golf.
You think this is not enough?

597
01:12:46,240 --> 01:12:49,084
I think it's enough.
- Interviewer: Your life.

598
01:12:49,240 --> 01:12:53,370
All my life. And life is more important
than anything else, right?

599
01:12:53,520 --> 01:12:55,648
So golf owes me something.

600
01:12:56,880 --> 01:13:01,124
Or maybe we're even--
but I don't owe anything to golf.

601
01:14:22,760 --> 01:14:24,842
(ﬂute music)

602
01:14:47,680 --> 01:14:49,762
(cows moo)

603
01:15:15,920 --> 01:15:17,490
Father: Ho, ho!

604
01:15:20,840 --> 01:15:22,922
(music fades out)

605
01:15:23,120 --> 01:15:25,441
Man:

606
01:15:34,000 --> 01:15:35,081
(laughs)

607
01:16:38,640 --> 01:16:41,928
Brother: (Spanish)

608
01:17:01,720 --> 01:17:03,802
(murmuring) (chatting)

609
01:17:23,120 --> 01:17:25,248
(applause)

610
01:17:32,680 --> 01:17:34,250
All: Seve! Seve!

611
01:17:45,440 --> 01:17:48,887
As we were going out on the last day, Seve said:

612
01:17:49,040 --> 01:17:51,850
"The one with the biggest heart will win,"

613
01:17:52,720 --> 01:17:55,451
<i>I thought, well, you mean you, don't you.</i>

614
01:17:57,080 --> 01:17:59,162
(piano music)

615
01:18:04,040 --> 01:18:05,326
(hit)

616
01:18:05,480 --> 01:18:07,562
(music becomes more rhythmic)

617
01:18:15,360 --> 01:18:17,647
(acoustic guitar joins in)

618
01:18:22,840 --> 01:18:23,887
(hit)

619
01:18:30,840 --> 01:18:33,446
Broadcaster: Well, that is pure magic.

620
01:18:35,240 --> 01:18:40,610
Seve: When I walk into the ball
and I see the line and I see the shot,

621
01:18:40,760 --> 01:18:45,482
it was very difficult if I say, okay,
let's play one of those shots

622
01:18:45,640 --> 01:18:47,768
that you did when you were young.

623
01:18:47,920 --> 01:18:50,321
(applause)

624
01:18:50,480 --> 01:18:52,448
Broadcaster: A touch of genius!

625
01:18:53,800 --> 01:18:54,847
(hit)

626
01:19:00,240 --> 01:19:03,130
Seve: From the background
I would have nothing.

627
01:19:03,280 --> 01:19:06,887
Remember, I had no balls. No clubs.
No money, nothing.

628
01:19:07,040 --> 01:19:11,443
I used to make bets without having any
pennies in my pocket.

629
01:19:14,640 --> 01:19:17,371
I had no choice. I had to win somehow.

630
01:19:19,000 --> 01:19:22,561
So obviously I became a tremendous competitor.

631
01:19:25,520 --> 01:19:27,921
Dave Musgrove:
If somebody's playing good,

632
01:19:28,080 --> 01:19:32,768
we say: he obviously has no money
because he can't afford to lose.

633
01:19:32,920 --> 01:19:37,687
That was Seve's attitude. He had no money.
Every week. And he expects to win.

634
01:20:03,120 --> 01:20:06,681
Dave Musgrove: If you caddied for him
for a while, you knew

635
01:20:06,840 --> 01:20:09,730
he could simply handle anything and anybody.

636
01:20:09,880 --> 01:20:13,566
<i>People thought it was a prestigious position...</i>
<i>But it wasn't.</i>

637
01:20:13,720 --> 01:20:17,281
He made us realize that all day and every day.

638
01:20:20,160 --> 01:20:22,766
After he won the Open, the next time I saw him

639
01:20:22,960 --> 01:20:25,645
he handed me a list of things I had done wrong.

640
01:20:43,880 --> 01:20:47,327
Dave Musgrove: "Run after the ball!"
Over the hill.

641
01:20:47,480 --> 01:20:50,848
When I got there he'd go:
"Where have you been?"

642
01:20:54,160 --> 01:20:56,003
He never rested on his laurels.

643
01:20:56,200 --> 01:21:00,569
Maybe because he's the youngest of four,
and he always had to prove himself.

644
01:21:00,720 --> 01:21:02,290
(hit)

645
01:21:15,240 --> 01:21:18,244
Seve: I control my emotions really well.

646
01:21:18,400 --> 01:21:21,165
That always has been my strongest point.

647
01:21:25,960 --> 01:21:30,807
It's part of the game. If you cannot
control your emotions, you cannot play.

648
01:21:40,560 --> 01:21:42,210
(Silent)

649
01:22:11,000 --> 01:22:14,721
Seve: I say to myself,
this is your tournament.

650
01:22:14,880 --> 01:22:18,407
It may sound wife bit arrogant, but I expect to win.

651
01:22:23,480 --> 01:22:25,244
(all cheer)

652
01:22:25,400 --> 01:22:27,482
(applause)

653
01:22:27,640 --> 01:22:30,291
Brother: Congratulations, little brother!

654
01:22:32,240 --> 01:22:35,801
Seve: <i>When I play good I have so much fun
and so much pleasure</i>

655
01:22:35,960 --> 01:22:39,169
that there's no money in the world that can pay that.

656
01:22:56,560 --> 01:22:59,291
(music fades into slow string music)

657
01:23:41,600 --> 01:23:43,682
(festive music fades in)

658
01:23:59,920 --> 01:24:01,843
(Spanish)

659
01:24:31,720 --> 01:24:34,041
(crackling) (all cheer)

660
01:24:39,040 --> 01:24:41,122
(exploding)

661
01:24:55,400 --> 01:24:57,607
Seve:

662
01:24:57,760 --> 01:24:58,841
Rafa:

663
01:25:02,080 --> 01:25:04,242
Rafa: Come on, Seve!

664
01:25:08,560 --> 01:25:10,801
(shouting)

665
01:25:14,240 --> 01:25:16,322
BOY?

666
01:25:19,440 --> 01:25:20,680
Seve:

667
01:25:20,880 --> 01:25:23,804
Boys:

668
01:25:24,800 --> 01:25:26,006
(they laugh)

669
01:25:43,600 --> 01:25:44,647
(hit)

670
01:25:47,240 --> 01:25:48,287
Rafa:

671
01:26:25,080 --> 01:26:26,127
Mother:

672
01:26:31,360 --> 01:26:35,604
Seve: My father was always telling me
that I would be a good golfer

673
01:26:35,760 --> 01:26:41,210
and he always said "keep going, you look
great and you have the power.

674
01:26:41,360 --> 01:26:43,931
You'll be great and golf is very easy."

675
01:26:44,960 --> 01:26:47,804
He'd say those things.
And that helps.

676
01:26:49,320 --> 01:26:52,403
My mother tried to find me a job
- A safe job.

677
01:26:54,360 --> 01:26:57,443
Maybe go and work in a factory

678
01:26:57,600 --> 01:27:01,366
or maybe study and be a lawyer or something else.

679
01:27:01,520 --> 01:27:05,445
But a safe position, you know.

680
01:28:02,600 --> 01:28:03,886
Sergio:

681
01:28:19,560 --> 01:28:20,800
Father:

682
01:28:21,720 --> 01:28:24,883
Mother:

683
01:28:47,680 --> 01:28:50,729
Father:

684
01:29:09,920 --> 01:29:11,285
Father:

685
01:29:22,640 --> 01:29:24,369
Brother:

686
01:30:10,560 --> 01:30:11,800
Brother:

687
01:30:37,920 --> 01:30:41,129
Brother:

688
01:30:44,080 --> 01:30:46,287
(light-hearted music fades in)

689
01:30:49,160 --> 01:30:51,925
Broadcaster:
On a warm, wind/ass Sunday,

690
01:30:52,080 --> 01:30:55,323
four men arrive for one of golf's great finishes.

691
01:30:55,480 --> 01:30:57,562
(they greet each other)

692
01:31:03,000 --> 01:31:06,607
Interviewer: How are you today?
- Pretty good, it's a beautiful day.

693
01:31:07,760 --> 01:31:10,809
Fan: We're pulling for you, Jack!
- Oh, thank you.

694
01:31:10,960 --> 01:31:12,769
- Fan: You play well!
- I'll try.

695
01:31:12,920 --> 01:31:17,528
Who do you think might win this Masters?
Would you pick a champion?

696
01:31:17,680 --> 01:31:22,402
I don't think you can ever win doing that
but Ballesteros will probably win

697
01:31:22,560 --> 01:31:25,848
because he is definitely the best player in the world.

698
01:31:30,000 --> 01:31:33,766
Seve: This is one thing that I have.
I have it in my heart.

699
01:31:34,560 --> 01:31:36,210
(hit)

700
01:31:37,480 --> 01:31:41,530
Seve: Coming into the Masters,
I didn't have a chance to practice

701
01:31:41,720 --> 01:31:43,529
because my father was sick.

702
01:31:43,720 --> 01:31:46,451
Broadcaster: Here it comes!

703
01:31:48,360 --> 01:31:50,966
Seve: I did promise my father. I said:

704
01:31:51,120 --> 01:31:56,923
"I want you to come to the Masters because
this year I am going to win it for you."

705
01:31:58,800 --> 01:32:01,690
I never thought he was going to die so early.

706
01:32:03,480 --> 01:32:09,044
He passed away the 5th of March
and I went to play the Masters

707
01:32:09,200 --> 01:32:13,683
with only nine rounds of competition in six months.

708
01:32:16,920 --> 01:32:19,048
Broadcaster: Seve for an Eagle.

709
01:32:20,960 --> 01:32:24,203
What a moment. What a moment to do it.

710
01:32:24,360 --> 01:32:26,169
(applause)

711
01:32:30,560 --> 01:32:33,131
I'm standing in the middle of the field on the 15th,

712
01:32:35,000 --> 01:32:37,002
and I hit a four onto the green.

713
01:32:38,000 --> 01:32:40,287
(crowd cheering)

714
01:32:40,440 --> 01:32:44,968
Broadcaster: And he's got a chance.
He's got a very, very good chance

715
01:32:46,080 --> 01:32:49,801
of an Eagle three to make him seven under par.

716
01:32:51,520 --> 01:32:55,491
Yes, Sir!
And the old bear is back!

717
01:32:57,520 --> 01:33:01,047
<i>Jack Nicklaus, knowing he must continue the charge.</i>

718
01:33:01,200 --> 01:33:06,240
He has to figure that Ballesteros
will make at least Birdie back al fifteen.

719
01:33:06,400 --> 01:33:08,482
(applause)

720
01:33:11,800 --> 01:33:14,326
Oh my. And there's no doubt about it.

721
01:33:14,520 --> 01:33:18,161
The bear has come out of hibernation.

722
01:33:19,000 --> 01:33:24,609
Obviously, Jack played fantastic
down the straights on the last five holes,

723
01:33:24,760 --> 01:33:28,890
but I was two shots ahead and I hit
a beautiful tee shot on the 15th.

724
01:33:29,080 --> 01:33:31,765
(cheering)

725
01:33:31,920 --> 01:33:34,321
Sever And I have to wait a little bit.

726
01:33:35,960 --> 01:33:38,486
He had the feeling that, until that point,

727
01:33:38,640 --> 01:33:43,202
it he really wanted to win something
he could dictate: I'm going to win this.

728
01:33:44,520 --> 01:33:48,127
The tournament will be over before the 16th this year.

729
01:33:48,920 --> 01:33:52,686
Interviewer: I don't need to ask how.
- My way. Of course.

730
01:33:56,600 --> 01:34:01,049
<i>Broadcaster: Right now, it is
Seve Ballesteros's Masters to lose.</i>

731
01:34:01,200 --> 01:34:03,328
(suspenseful music)

732
01:34:03,480 --> 01:34:05,005
(hit)

733
01:34:05,200 --> 01:34:08,602
Broadcaster: That was the worst shot
I've seen him hit...

734
01:34:09,960 --> 01:34:11,530
He got it in the water.

735
01:34:11,680 --> 01:34:15,366
He let go of the club. It looks like
something happened there.

736
01:34:15,520 --> 01:34:21,243
That's absolutely extraordinary. I don't
think We ever seen him hit such a shot.

737
01:34:21,400 --> 01:34:25,371
<i>Jack Nicklaus: He's on the 17th tee
and Seve hits it into the water.</i>

738
01:34:25,520 --> 01:34:29,081
And I heard the sound.
I knew exactly what it was.

739
01:34:29,240 --> 01:34:33,768
Because it was the sound of not cheering,
but some groaning...

740
01:34:35,400 --> 01:34:38,483
I guess that was the destiny for me--
not to win.

741
01:34:41,240 --> 01:34:42,969
Broadcaster: Maybe”.

742
01:34:43,120 --> 01:34:44,849
Yes, Sir!

743
01:34:45,000 --> 01:34:47,446
(applause)

744
01:34:52,000 --> 01:34:55,527
Seve: It was great,
the way Jack Nicklaus played.

745
01:34:57,560 --> 01:35:02,885
But the bitterness that I have inside my body

