749
01:35:38,440 --> 01:35:41,250
But being back at Lytham inspired him.

750
01:35:42,280 --> 01:35:43,850
How are you?

751
01:35:51,680 --> 01:35:54,081
The greatest I saw him play

752
01:35:54,240 --> 01:35:55,571
(hit)

753
01:35:55,720 --> 01:35:58,929
was that Monday when Pricey and I

754
01:35:59,080 --> 01:36:00,650
and Seve went oh'.

755
01:36:03,960 --> 01:36:06,611
Broadcaster: Now this could play in”.

756
01:36:07,440 --> 01:36:09,124
(applause)

757
01:36:09,320 --> 01:36:13,041
Broadcaster: He can'! see the bottom of
the ﬂag, so that's not bad.

758
01:36:13,240 --> 01:36:15,925
Nick Faldo: When you see a guy playing

759
01:36:16,120 --> 01:36:20,762
when they're just unbelievable.
And that was probably his finest day.

760
01:36:20,960 --> 01:36:22,724
(crowd cheers)

761
01:36:22,920 --> 01:36:26,402
Nick Faldo: That was the day
when he was the true Seve.

762
01:36:26,560 --> 01:36:29,643
He pieced together that round and I said to him:

763
01:36:29,840 --> 01:36:32,730
"That was the best round of golf
I've ever seen."

764
01:36:33,680 --> 01:36:37,526
Seve and! distanced ourselves
from the rest of the field

765
01:36:37,680 --> 01:36:41,730
toward the end of the front nine and we
